  {
    "type": "text",
    "text": "Prediction: ",
    "bbox": [
      220,
      667,
      243,
      681
    ],
    "page_idx": 0
  },
  {
    "type": "equation",
    "text": "$$\n\\mu (y \\mid \\mathcal {G} _ {i}) = \\frac {1}{K} \\sum_ {k = 1} ^ {K} f _ {\\theta} ([ \\mathcal {G} _ {i}, c _ {k} ])\n$$",
    "text_format": "latex",
    "bbox": [
      220,
      680,
      302,
      716
    ],
    "page_idx": 0,
    "img_path": ""
  },
  {
    "type": "text",
    "text": "Uncertainty: ",
    "bbox": [
      219,
      721,
      247,
      733
    ],
    "page_idx": 0
  },
  {
    "type": "equation",
    "text": "$$\n\\boldsymbol {\\sigma} (y \\mid \\mathcal {G} _ {i}) = \\sqrt {\\frac {1}{K - 1} \\sum_ {k = 1} ^ {K} \\left(f _ {\\theta} \\left(\\left[ \\mathcal {G} _ {i} , c _ {k} \\right]\\right) - \\boldsymbol {\\mu}\\right) ^ {2}}\n$$",
    "text_format": "latex",
    "bbox": [
      220,
      734,
      313,
      773
    ],
    "page_idx": 0,
    "img_path": ""
  },
  {
    "type": "text",
    "text": "Calibrated Prediction: ",
    "bbox": [
      218,
      785,
      270,
      797
    ],
    "page_idx": 0
  },
  {
    "type": "equation",
    "text": "$$\n\\boldsymbol {\\mu} _ {c a l i b} = \\boldsymbol {\\mu} (1 - \\sigma)\n$$",
    "text_format": "latex",
    "bbox": [
      236,
      802,
      290,
      819
    ],
    "page_idx": 0,
    "img_path": ""
  },
  {
    "type": "list",
    "sub_type": "text",
    "list_items": [
      "· Since graphs are variable sized and discrete,we introduce three anchoring strategies tailored for GNNs. ",
      "· Induce varying levels of stochasticity, trading off hypothesis diversity and the semantic diversity of the anchoring distribution. "
    ],
    "bbox": [
      5,
      875,
      309,
      975
    ],
    "page_idx": 0
  },
